commitResults.messageBody:
Level-1: Greet, Echo, Exit
* created printLine()
* created greet()
* created echo()
* created exit()

Level 2. Add, List
* Added a private arrayList attribute to Duke
* Added the ability to store whatever text entered by user
* Added the ability to display the stored text back to the user

Level-3: Mark as Done

Changes to Duke.java
* modify and renamed lst attribute in duke to contain Task Object
* add indentation to text to be displayed
* create the retrieveTask method to retrieve Task from attribute
* create markOrUnmarked to mark or unmark tasks

New Task.java file
* add new Task class to support representation of tasks

Improved Duke.java
* Removed unnecessary System.out.println() calls and
  depend more on echo().
* implemented the extractStr method to extract specific
  substrings from a string, to extract description and date.

Added 3 different types of Tasks
* Event, DeadLine and ToDo are subclasses of Task, using
  inheritance will later help us to make use of polymorphism
  when dealing with different types of Tasks in the arrayList.

* Included some input for text-ui-test
* Included expected ouput for FC
* Conducted automated testing of DUKE.
* Actual input matches expected output.

* Created DukeException class
* Added try catch blocks to handle errors thrown by Duke

* Created the delete task method.
* Continue to use ArrayList.

* Fix bugs in extracting description and date
* Conducted additional automated testings

Added more error handlings such as
if integer is not provided to mark or unmark.
